[SN]TITLE[SN]
Whalley Range crash: Boy, 17, admits deaths by dangerous driving

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 17-year-old boy has admitted causing the deaths of three men by dangerous driving and seriously injuring a fourth person.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 20, 21 and 24-year-olds died as a result of a crash on Wilbraham Road in Whalley Range, Manchester.
An Audi collided with two parked cars on 27 April.
The youth, who cannot be named, will be sentenced at Manchester Crown Court on 15 July.
He pleaded guilty to three counts of death by dangerous driving and one count of causing serious injury by dangerous driving.
